import{_ as e,o,c as t,a,b as r}from"./app-a6eacc5a.js";const s={},n=r('<h1 id="dream-robot" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#dream-robot" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Dream Robot</h1><p>Japanese engineer Masaaki Nagumo had always dreamed of operating a robot from &quot;Mobile Suit Gundam.&quot;</p><p>That is the name of a popular Japanese animation television series. It was Nagumo&#39;s favorite show when he was a child. The series features huge, human-controlled machines in battle.</p><p>Now Nagumo has made the show come to life. He has built a large robot <code>inspired</code> by the machines.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 日本工程师南云正章（Masaaki Nagumo）一直梦想着操作《机动战士高达》中的机器人。</p><p>《机动战士高达》是日本一部热门的动画电视连续剧，这是南云正章小时候最喜欢的节目。这部电视剧以人类操控巨大的机器对战为特色。</p><p>现在南云正章让这个节目变成了现实。受这些机器的启发，他建造了一台大型机器人。</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> inspire ( inspiring, inspired, inspires )<br><code>英 [ɪnˈspaɪə(r)]美 [ɪnˈspaɪər]</code></p><blockquote><p>v. 激励，鼓舞；赋予灵感，激发（想法）；使产生（感觉或情感）；引起，导致；吸气，吸入</p></blockquote></details><p>The robot is called LW-Mononofu. The farming <code>machinery</code> company Sakakibara Kikai developed it. The robot is 8.5 meters tall, has two legs and weighs more than seven <code>metric</code> tons. It has a seating area with <code>monitors</code>, and devices for the <code>pilot</code> to be able control the robot&#39;s arms and legs.</p><p>The 44-year-old Nagumo spoke to the Reuters <em>news agency</em> about the popularity of the &quot;Mobile Suit Gundam&quot; series. It inspired movies, manga, video games and more. And so, he suggested the robot could be popular as well.</p><p>&quot;I think this can be turned into a <em>business <code>opportunity</code></em>,&quot; Nagumo said.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 该机器人被称之为LW武士，由日本榊原农业机械公司所开发。该机器人身高8.5米，有两条腿，重量超过7吨。它的座舱拥有监视器以及让驾驶员能够操控机器人的胳膊和腿的各种装置。</p><p>44岁的南云正章向路透社谈到了《机动战士高达》电视剧的受欢迎程度。它衍生出了电影、漫画、视频游戏等等。他透露因此这台机器人可能也会很受欢迎。</p><p>南云正章表示:“我认为这可以转化为商机。”</p><p><strong>phrase:</strong><br> news agency -&gt; 新闻社：向订阅的报纸、期刊和新闻播音员提供新闻的组织。<br> business opportunity -&gt; 商业机会：销售或租赁任何产品、服务、设备等，使购买者-许可证持有人能够开始一项业务。</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> machinery<br><code>英 [məˈʃiːnəri]美 [məˈʃiːnəri]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 机器，机械（尤指大型机械）；体系，机制；运转部份，装置</p></blockquote><p>metric [ 复数 metrics ]<br><code>英 [ˈmetrɪk]美 [ˈmetrɪk]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 米制的，公制的；度规的；用诗体写的，格律诗的<br> n. 诗韵；衡量标准；度规</p></blockquote><p>monitor ( monitoring, monitored, monitors )<br><code>英 [ˈmɒnɪtə(r)]美 [ˈmɑːnɪtər]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 显示器，监控器；监视仪，监护仪；监督员，监察员；（学校里的）班长，级长；（电台的）监听员；扬声器；巨蜥；浅水重炮舰<br> v. 监视；监听（外国广播或电话）；监控（无线电或电视传输信号）</p></blockquote><p>pilot ( piloting, piloted, pilots )<br><code>英 [ˈpaɪlət]美 [ˈpaɪlət]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 飞行员；领航员；（船只的）领航员；（电视）试播节目；常燃小火；航海手册；&lt;非正式&gt;职业骑师；&lt;古&gt;向导；（火车头前端的）排障器<br> adj. 试点的；（电信）控制引导信号<br> v. 驾驶（飞行器）；领航；试验，试行；使（新法律）顺利通过；&lt;文&gt;带领，指引</p></blockquote><p>opportunity [ 复数 opportunities ]<br><code>英 [ˌɒpəˈtjuːnəti]美 [ˌɑːpərˈtuːnəti]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 时机，机会</p></blockquote></details><p>Sakakibara Kikai develops robots and entertainment machines <em>in addition to</em> its main <code>agriculture</code> equipment business. For a rate of about $930 an hour, people can rent the machines for children&#39;s birthday parties and other events, Nagumo said.</p><p>The company has created robots of all sizes. There is the almost 3.5-meter-tall Landwalker, the smaller Kid&#39;s Walker Cyclops, and the MechBoxer boxing machine.</p><p>But the Mononofu <em>stands above</em> them all. It also does more complex movements. It can move its fingers and turn its upper body, and walk forward and backward. However, it moves very slowly - at a speed of less than one kilometer per hour.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 榊原农业机械公司在主营的农业设备业务之外，还开发机器人和游艺机。南云正章表示，人们可以以每小时930美元的价格租用这些机器用于儿童生日派对等活动。</p><p>该公司制造了各种规格的机器人。有3.5米高的 Landwalker，较小型的儿童版独眼巨人以及 MechBoxer 拳击机器。</p><p>但是LW武士在他们之上，还能做更复杂的动作。它可以移动手指并转动上半身，可以前后走动。但是它的移动速度非常缓慢，速度不到一公里每小时。</p><p><strong>phrase：</strong><br> in addition to -&gt; 除了……之外：表示在已经提到的事物之外，还有额外的事物或观点。<br> stands above -&gt; 高于；超过：在某方面或某种标准上超过其他事物或人。</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> agriculture<br><code>英 [ˈæɡrɪkʌltʃə(r)]美 [ˈæɡrɪkʌltʃər]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 农业，农学，农艺</p></blockquote></details><p>Although it may be slow, the Mononofu is very powerful. The <code>bazooka</code>-like air gun on its right arm shoots balls of soft material at 140 kilometers per hour. &quot;As an <code>anime</code>-inspired robot that one can ride, I think this is the biggest in the world,&quot; Nagumo said. But Mononofu might be a bit too large.</p><p>It is unable to leave the factory without being <em>taken apart</em> because it was built taller than the entrance.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 虽然LW武士可能很缓慢，但是它非常强大。它右臂的火箭筒状气枪可以以每小时140公里的速度发射软质球体。南云正章表示:“我认为这是全球最大的可骑行动漫衍生机器人。”但是LW武士可能个头有点太大了。</p><p>由于它造出来比入口还要高，如果不拆开，它就没法离开工厂。</p><p><strong>phrase:</strong><br> taken apart -&gt; 1．拆卸：将（某物）的各个部分分开。 / 2．粗暴对待，严厉批评：对（某人或某物）粗暴或严厉地对待或批评。</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> bazooka [ 复数 bazookas ]<br><code>英 [bəˈzuːkə]美 [bəˈzuːkə]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 火箭炮；长号式笛子；（反坦克）巴祖卡火箭筒</p></blockquote><p>anime<br><code>英 [ˈænɪmeɪ]美 [ˈænɪmeɪˌˈɑːnimeɪ]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 日本动画片（常以科幻为主题）；芳香树脂</p></blockquote></details>',16);function i(p,l){return o(),t("div",null,[a(" 日本工程师造出梦想中的大型机器人 "),n])}const d=e(s,[["render",i],["__file","22-dream-robot.html.vue"]]);export{d as default};
